  "texts": [
    "These advances have significantly broadened access to fine-tuning billion-parameter models.Prefix-tuning and adapters.",
    "Earlier PEFT approaches, including prefix tuning, prompt tuning, and lightweight adapters [5,6], involve learning small additional components (prefix tokens, prompts, or bottleneck layers) while keeping the original model frozen.",
    "These methods are computationally efficient and introduce far fewer parameters compared to full fine-tuning.",
    "However, they often underperform compared to LoRA in tasks that require substantial model adaptation, as they provide less representational flexibility and struggle to capture complex reasoning patterns or domain-specific knowledge that demands deeper adjustments in model parameters.",
    "Rank Adaptation TechniquesWhile LoRA and QLoRA use a fixed adapter rank across all layers and throughout training, recent research has investigated techniques for adaptive rank allocation to make better use of the available parameter budget."
  ],
